volumeMounted.name: volumeMounted
volumeMounted.description: The number of volumes that are currently mounted on the system.

volumeEntry.name: volumeEntry
volumeEntry.description: Each entry contains objects that define the volume.

volumeLDEV.name: volumeLDEV
volumeLDEV.description: The logical device number for the volume.

volumeName.name: volumeName
volumeName.description: This is the volume set name combined with the member name that uniquely distinguishes the actual volume on the system.

volumeDriveType.name: volumeDriveType
volumeDriveType.description: The type of the actual hardware device, e.g. HP7935.

volumeSectorSize.name: volumeSectorSize
volumeSectorSize.description: The logical sector size of the volume in bytes

volumeCapacity.name: volumeCapacity
volumeCapacity.description: The capacity of the volume in sectors.

volumeMPEOverhead.name: volumeMPEOverhead
volumeMPEOverhead.description: The total overhead which consists of everything on a volume that is not set aside for file space use. This includes volume label, file label table, directory, volume set information table, free space map, transient space, and transaction management overhead.

volumeMPETransOverhead.name: volumeMPETransOverhead
volumeMPETransOverhead.description: The total MPE XL transient space overhead for the volume.

volumeMPEConfigMaxTrans.name: volumeMPEConfigMaxTrans
volumeMPEConfigMaxTrans.description: The configured maximum transient space for the volume.

volumeDirSpaceOverhead.name: volumeDirSpaceOverhead
volumeDirSpaceOverhead.description: The directory space overhead that is reserved for accounting information.

volumeFileLabelOverhead.name: volumeFileLabelOverhead
volumeFileLabelOverhead.description: The file label overhead for this volume.

volumeTransactionMgmtOverhead.name: volumeTransactionMgmtOverhead
volumeTransactionMgmtOverhead.description: The transaction management overhead for this volume.

volumeSpoolFileDiscUsage.name: volumeSpoolFileDiscUsage
volumeSpoolFileDiscUsage.description: The spool file disc space usage which consists of the volume space that is used by hidden spool files that are not part of the permanent file space.

volumePermFiles.name: volumePermFiles
volumePermFiles.description: The space used for permanent files on this volume.

volumeTempFiles.name: volumeTempFiles
volumeTempFiles.description: The space used for temporary files on this volume.

volumeTotalFreeSpace.name: volumeTotalFreeSpace
volumeTotalFreeSpace.description: The total free space for the volume.

volumeLargestContigFree.name: volumeLargestContigFree
volumeLargestContigFree.description: The largest contiguous free space area on the volume.

volumePercentUtilized.name: volumePercentUtilized
volumePercentUtilized.description: The percent of the volume currently being used for file storage and operating system overhead.

numActive.name: numActive
numActive.description: Number of processors currently active, in the system. A processor is considered active if it is capable of begin dispatched.

numPresent.name: numPresent
numPresent.description: The number of processors physically present in the system.

processorMIstate.name: processorMIstate
processorMIstate.description: Setting this object to 1 will result in the measurement interface being turned on for the global processor statistics which will increase the amount of CPU used by the SNMP/XL Agent. Setting this object to 0 will cause the measurement interface to be disabled for the global processor statistics. When the measurement interface is enabled, the cpuUtilization object described below may be obtained.

cpuUtilization.name: cpuUtilization
cpuUtilization.description: The overall CPU utilization percentage on the system. If the system has more than one processor, the value returned is averaged out over all of the processors that are present. The measurement interface must be enabled in order to get a valid value returned for this object ( see above object ). The number returned is the percentage of the CPU that was used since the last time the number was sampled. This value is consistent with various HP performance tools such as Glance/XL. If the measurement interface is not enabled, the value returned will be 0.
